#Dropping columns that are highly correlated to each other
corr_abs = corr.abs()
# upper triangle of correlation matrix
upper_triangle = corr_abs.where(np.triu(np.ones(corr_abs.shape), k=1).astype(np.bool))
dropped = [col for col in upper_triangle.columns if any(upper_triangle[col] > 0.85)]
df = df.drop(dropped, axis = 1)
